You can find all modules under /lib/modules/n.n

> uname -r  shows current running kernel

> cd /lib/modules/n.n
> insmod kernel/...ko.xz    load a module
> insmod -f kernel/...ko.xz    load a module even if not same version

> modprobe MODULE   like insmode only better
                        name, dependency, params

> lsmod     shows current loaded modules

> lspci -k  shows connected hardware and wich kernel module
            should be used / is used

> rmmod     removes module
> modinfo   shows module info

